what I'm saying?

515
00:29:43,848 --> 00:29:45,516
Yes, I do.

516
00:29:47,351 --> 00:29:49,252
I'm all right.

517
00:29:49,286 --> 00:29:51,821
And thank you.

518
00:29:51,855 --> 00:29:55,125
So you have a nice night.
And I'm gonna go prepare.

519
00:30:05,868 --> 00:30:08,570
- Say good night to your friend.
- Good luck tomorrow.

520
00:30:27,722 --> 00:30:31,759
<i>You must get tired of hearing
what a beautiful thing this car is.</i>

521
00:30:31,793 --> 00:30:34,061
But I've met a lot
of beautiful women in my life.

522
00:30:34,095 --> 00:30:36,730
And despite
their protestations,

523
00:30:36,765 --> 00:30:38,699
they never tire of hearing it.

524
00:30:40,135 --> 00:30:43,336
But when deep beauty
is encountered,

525
00:30:43,371 --> 00:30:46,606
it arouses deep emotions

526
00:30:46,641 --> 00:30:50,010
because it creates a desire,

527
00:30:50,045 --> 00:30:53,179
<i>because it is, by nature,</i>
<i>unattainable.</i>

528
00:30:53,213 --> 00:30:55,214
You look radiant, Joan.

529
00:30:55,248 --> 00:30:57,884
May I call you Joan?
I'm Herb, by the way.

530
00:30:57,918 --> 00:31:00,553
Well, I should hope so.

531
00:31:00,587 --> 00:31:04,090
We're taught to think that
function is all that matters.

532
00:31:04,124 --> 00:31:07,126
But we have a natural longing

533
00:31:07,161 --> 00:31:09,327
for this other thing.

534
00:31:09,361 --> 00:31:12,630
Oh, I got you
